adding":"6px 14px","borderRadius":"100px","display":"inline-block"},"children":[86," events listed"]}]}]]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"page-px sport-content-inner","style":{"maxWidth":"1280px","margin":"0 auto","paddingTop":"32px","paddingBottom":"60px"},"children":["$","$L3",null,{"sport":{"slug":"cricket","name":"Cricket","icon":"🏏","count":86,"description":"Test matches, ODIs, T20s — from the Ashes to the IPL. Compare cricket ticket prices.","color":"#10b981","isFeatured":true,"metaTitle":"Cricket Tickets | Ashes, T20 World Cup & Test Matches | TicketNexus","metaDescription":"Compare cricket ticket prices for the Ashes, T20 World Cup, IPL and England Test matches. Find the best deals on cricket tickets from trusted platforms.","metaKeywords":"cricket tickets, Ashes tickets, T20 World Cup tickets, IPL tickets, Test match tickets, buy cricket tickets, cricket ticket comparison"},"allEvents":[],"newsArticles":[{"id":"6","slug":"cricket-test-match-best-seats","title":"England Cricket 2025: The Best Seats at Lord's, The Oval, and Edgbaston","snippet":"Which end is best for watching Test cricket? Our ground-by-ground breakdown of the best viewing positions and how to book them.","category":"cricket","icon":"🏏","author":"Anika Sharma","authorAvatar":"/images/17a0fc2f15c2417e.jpg","publishedAt":"2025-02-05","addedon":"2025-02-05","leagueSlug":"t20-world-cup","readTime":6,"imageUrl":"/images/de1231d6f8156af5.jpg","imageCaption":"Lord's Cricket Ground in St John's Wood is the spiritual home of cricket worldwide. (Getty Images)","keyPoints":["County membership provides priority booking windows of up to 4 weeks before general sale","The Eric Hollies Stand at Edgbaston consistently sells out first — book immediately on release","Day five Edgbaston tickets are sometimes offered free if the match reaches a likely conclusion early"],"metaTitle":"Best Seats for Test Cricket 2025: Lord's, The Oval & Edgbaston Guide","metaDescription":"Find the best seats for England Test cricket at Lord's, The Oval, and Edgbaston in 2025. Ground-by-ground breakdown with booking tips and pricing.","metaKeywords":"cricket tickets 2025, Lord's cricket tickets, The Oval tickets, Edgbaston tickets, England Test match tickets, best cricket seats, buy cricket tickets","content":[{"h2":"Lord's Cricket Ground: Where to Sit for the Full Experience","body":"Lord's is unlike any other cricket ground in the world, and choosing where to sit requires understanding its unique character. The Compton Stand offers the purest cricket view with the Pavilion directly behind the bowler's arm from the Pavilion End — ideal for reading line and length. The Grandstand and Edrich Stand provide a broader panoramic view at a slightly higher price point. The Warner Stand is popular for its central position but can be impacted by the famous Lord's slope which tilts the whole playing surface by 2.5 metres. Avoid the Nursery End upper tier if you prioritise an unobstructed view of the iconic Pavilion backdrop."},{"h2":"The Oval: Best Stands for Atmosphere and Visibility","body":"The Kia Oval in Kennington, London is a ground where the atmosphere consistently outperforms expectations for a city venue. The OCS Stand runs along the pavilion side and offers some of the best sightlines in English cricket from the middle and upper tiers. For those who prefer a livelier atmosphere, the Bedser Stand opposite fills quickly with a knowledgeable crowd and is cheaper than the OCS equivalent. The most memorable seats in the ground are in the lower Pavilion, directly behind the bowler's arm — but these are members-only for the first three days of each Test."},{"h2":"Edgbaston: The Loudest Ground in England","body":"Edgbaston in Birmingham has cemented its reputation as England's most vocal Test cricket venue, with the Eric Hollies Stand generating an atmosphere that commentators regularly compare to a football ground. Seats in the Eric Hollies Stand are the cheapest at the ground, extremely popular, and frequently sell out first — book as soon as they go on sale. For families, the Raglan Suite end offers covered seating and clearer sightlines without the boisterous element. The pavilion stands offer outstanding views down the pitch and are the choice of the ground's most serious cricket watchers."},{"h2":"How to Book England Cricket Tickets and Avoid Common Pitfalls","body":"England home Test tickets are sold exclusively through the ECB and the host county club. Membership of the host county (Middlesex for Lord's, Surrey for The Oval, Warwickshire for Edgbaston) provides priority booking windows of up to four weeks before general sale — for major series such as the Ashes, this is often the only viable route to sought-after seats. General sale dates are announced via the ECB website in the autumn. On the secondary market, FootballTicketNet and Awin carry legitimate resale inventory, but premiums of 80–120% above face value are common for Ashes Tests. Prices tend to soften only in the final week before each Test day."}]}]}]}]]}],["$","footer",null,{"className":"footer-outer","style":{"background":"var(--white)","borderTop":"1px solid var(--border-gray)"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"maxWidth":"1280px","margin":"0 auto","paddingBottom":"40px","borderBottom":"1px solid var(--border-gray)"},"className":"footer-main-grid","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-poppins, Poppins, sans-serif)","fontSize":"26px","fontWeight":700,"marginBottom":"12px","color":"var(--text-dark)"},"children":[["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"var(--primary)"},"children":"Ticket"}],"Nexus"]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"14px","color":"var(--text-gray)","lineHeight":1.7,"maxWidth":"300px","marginBottom":"20px"},"children":"The UK's leading sports ticket comparison site. We help fans find the best prices from trusted resale platforms — so you never overpay for a seat."}],["$","div",null,{"style":{"display":"flex","gap"